---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Use Cases - AnswerLayer"
  description="How different teams use AnswerLayer to unlock insights from their data."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h1 class="mb-lg">Use Cases</h1>
      <p class="text-lg" style="max-width: 600px;">
        Different teams use AnswerLayer in different ways.
        Here's how our customers are building with the platform.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Persona 1: Data & Analytics Teams -->
  <section class="section-sm" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border);">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="persona">
        <h2 class="persona-title">Data & Analytics Teams</h2>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Challenge</div>
          <p>
            Drowning in ad-hoc requests. Business users can't get answers
            without filing a ticket and waiting days. Dashboards are static and don't
            answer the follow-up questions.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Solution</div>
          <p>
            Deploy AnswerLayer as a self-serve analytics layer. Business users ask questions
            in plain English. The semantic layer ensures consistent definitions across the org.
            PII filtering protects sensitive customer data automatically.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Outcome</div>
          <p class="text-muted">
            80% reduction in analyst ticket volume. Time-to-insight drops from days to seconds.
            Data team focuses on high-value projects instead of ad-hoc requests.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Persona 2: AI Product Companies -->
  <section class="section-sm" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border);">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="persona">
        <h2 class="persona-title">AI Product Companies</h2>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Challenge</div>
          <p>
            Building analytics into a SaaS product. Don't want to build and maintain
            a data infrastructure layer. Need to support multiple customer databases
            without exposing raw SQL to the LLM.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Solution</div>
          <p>
            Embed AnswerLayer as the analytics backend. Each customer gets their own
            isolated semantic layer. The API returns structured data that feeds into
            your product's AI features. Multi-tenant isolation is built in.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Outcome</div>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Ship AI-powered analytics in weeks instead of months. No database
            infrastructure to maintain. Scales with your customer base.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Persona 3: Security-Conscious Organizations -->
  <section class="section-sm" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border);">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="persona">
        <h2 class="persona-title">Security-Conscious Organizations</h2>
        <p class="text-muted text-sm mb-lg">Healthcare, Finance, Government</p>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Challenge</div>
          <p>
            Need analytics capabilities but can't send data to external services.
            Strict compliance requirements around data residency and access controls.
            Must demonstrate audit trails for all data access.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Solution</div>
          <p>
            VPC deploymentâ€”AnswerLayer runs entirely in your cloud. Data never leaves
            your environment. PII filtering catches sensitive information before it's
            exposed. Full audit logging for compliance.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Outcome</div>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Analytics without compliance risk. Full audit trail satisfies regulatory
            requirements. Security review measured in weeks, not months.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Persona 4: Data Platform Teams -->
  <section class="section-sm" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border);">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <div class="persona">
        <h2 class="persona-title">Data Platform Teams</h2>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Challenge</div>
          <p>
            AI agents need database access, but you can't trust raw SQL generation.
            LLMs hallucinate column names, miss JOINs, and ignore business logic.
            Building guardrails from scratch takes months.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Solution</div>
          <p>
            Use the semantic layer as the abstraction between AI and data.
            AnswerLayer validates queries against the schema, blocks dangerous operations,
            and enforces row limits. You define the rules; AI follows them.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="persona-section">
          <div class="persona-label">Outcome</div>
          <p class="text-muted">
            Safe, accurate, controlled AI-to-database access. Guardrails built in,
            not bolted on. Your agents query data without risking the production database.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section text-center" style="border-top: 1px solid var(--border);">
    <div class="container container-narrow">
      <h2 class="mb-md">Which describes you?</h2>
      <p class="text-muted mb-lg">
        Tell us about your use case and we'll help you get started.
      </p>
      <div class="flex gap-md" style="justify-content: center;">
        <a href="https://app.getanswerlayer.com/sign-up" class="btn btn-primary">Get Started</a>
        <a href="mailto:hello@getanswerlayer.com" class="btn btn-link">Talk to Us</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
